# Routing and Navigation Patterns

## Route Configuration

### Route Names
Define all route names in [RoutesName](mdc:lib/routes/routes_name.dart):

```dart
class RoutesName {
  RoutesName._();
  
  // Auth Flow
  static const String splashView = '/splash';
  static const String signInView = '/sign-in';
  static const String signUpView = '/sign-up';
  static const String forgotPasswordView = '/forgot-password';
  static const String otpVerificationView = '/otp-verification';
  
  // Main App
  static const String homeView = '/home';
  static const String profileView = '/profile';
  static const String settingsView = '/settings';
}
```

### Route Definitions
Configure routes in [routes.dart](mdc:lib/routes/routes.dart):

```dart
List<GetPage> pages = [
  // Auth Flow Routes
  getPage(
    name: RoutesName.splashView,
    page: () => const SplashView(),
    binding: SplashBindings(),
  ),
  getPage(
    name: RoutesName.signInView,
    page: () => const SignInView(),
    binding: SignInBindings(),
  ),
  getPage(
    name: RoutesName.signUpView,
    page: () => const SignUpView(),
    binding: SignUpBindings(),
  ),
  
  // Main App Routes
  getPage(
    name: RoutesName.homeView,
    page: () => const HomeView(),
    binding: HomeBindings(),
  ),
];
```

### Helper Function
Use the `getPage` helper for consistent route creation:

```dart
GetPage getPage({
  String? name,
  GetPageBuilder? page,
  Bindings? binding,
  List<GetPage<dynamic>>? children,
}) {
  return GetPage(
    name: name!,
    page: page!,
    binding: binding,
    children: children ?? [],
  );
}
```

## Navigation Methods

### Basic Navigation
```dart
// Navigate to a new screen
Get.toNamed(RoutesName.signInView);

// Navigate with arguments
Get.toNamed(RoutesName.profileView, arguments: {'userId': '123'});

// Navigate and replace current screen
Get.offNamed(RoutesName.homeView);

// Navigate and clear all previous screens
Get.offAllNamed(RoutesName.splashView);

// Navigate back
Get.back();

// Navigate back with result
Get.back(result: 'success');
```

### Navigation with Arguments
```dart
// Sending arguments
Get.toNamed(
  RoutesName.detailView,
  arguments: {
    'id': 123,
    'title': 'Product Details',
    'data': productModel,
  },
);

// Receiving arguments
class DetailController extends BaseViewController {
  late int id;
  late String title;
  late ProductModel data;
  
  @override
  void onInit() {
    super.onInit();
    
    final args = Get.arguments as Map<String, dynamic>?;
    if (args != null) {
      id = args['id'] ?? 0;
      title = args['title'] ?? '';
      data = args['data'] ?? ProductModel();
    }
  }
}
```

### Navigation with Parameters
```dart
// Define route with parameters
getPage(
  name: '/product/:id',
  page: () => const ProductView(),
  binding: ProductBindings(),
);

// Navigate with parameters
Get.toNamed('/product/123');

// Access parameters in controller
class ProductController extends BaseViewController {
  late String productId;
  
  @override
  void onInit() {
    super.onInit();
    productId = Get.parameters['id'] ?? '';
  }
}
```

### Navigation with Query Parameters
```dart
// Navigate with query parameters
Get.toNamed(
  RoutesName.searchView,
  parameters: {
    'query': 'flutter',
    'category': 'mobile',
    'page': '1',
  },
);

// Access query parameters
class SearchController extends BaseViewController {
  late String query;
  late String category;
  late int page;
  
  @override
  void onInit() {
    super.onInit();
    query = Get.parameters['query'] ?? '';
    category = Get.parameters['category'] ?? '';
    page = int.tryParse(Get.parameters['page'] ?? '1') ?? 1;
  }
}
```

## Navigation Guards

### Route Middleware
Implement navigation guards for authentication and authorization:

```dart
class AuthMiddleware extends GetMiddleware {
  @override
  RouteSettings? redirect(String? route) {
    // Check if user is authenticated
    if (!Preferences.isLogged) {
      return RouteSettings(name: RoutesName.signInView);
    }
    return null; // Allow navigation
  }
}

// Apply middleware to protected routes
getPage(
  name: RoutesName.profileView,
  page: () => const ProfileView(),
  binding: ProfileBindings(),
  middlewares: [AuthMiddleware()],
);
```

### Conditional Navigation
```dart
class FeatureController extends BaseViewController {
  Future<void> navigateToFeature() async {
    // Check conditions before navigation
    if (await _checkPermissions()) {
      Get.toNamed(RoutesName.featureView);
    } else {
      AppSnackBar.error(message: 'Permission denied');
    }
  }
  
  Future<bool> _checkPermissions() async {
    // Check user permissions
    return true;
  }
}
```

## Nested Navigation

### Nested Routes
Define nested routes for complex navigation structures:

```dart
getPage(
  name: RoutesName.homeView,
  page: () => const HomeView(),
  binding: HomeBindings(),
  children: [
    getPage(
      name: RoutesName.dashboardView,
      page: () => const DashboardView(),
      binding: DashboardBindings(),
    ),
    getPage(
      name: RoutesName.analyticsView,
      page: () => const AnalyticsView(),
      binding: AnalyticsBindings(),
    ),
  ],
);
```

### Bottom Navigation
Implement bottom navigation with GetX:

```dart
class MainController extends BaseViewController {
  RxInt currentIndex = 0.obs;
  
  final List<Widget> pages = [
    HomeView(),
    SearchView(),
    FavoritesView(),
    ProfileView(),
  ];
  
  void changePage(int index) {
    currentIndex.value = index;
  }
}

class MainView extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return GetBuilder<MainController>(
      builder: (controller) => Scaffold(
        body: controller.pages[controller.currentIndex.value],
        bottomNavigationBar: BottomNavigationBar(
          currentIndex: controller.currentIndex.value,
          onTap: controller.changePage,
          items: [
            BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.home), label: 'Home'),
            BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.search), label: 'Search'),
            BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.favorite), label: 'Favorites'),
            BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.person), label: 'Profile'),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Dialog and Bottom Sheet Navigation

### Custom Dialogs
```dart
// Show custom dialog
Get.dialog(
  AlertDialog(
    title: Text('Confirm Action'),
    content: Text('Are you sure you want to proceed?'),
    actions: [
      TextButton(
        onPressed: () => Get.back(),
        child: Text('Cancel'),
      ),
      ElevatedButton(
        onPressed: () {
          Get.back();
          _performAction();
        },
        child: Text('Confirm'),
      ),
    ],
  ),
);

// Show dialog with result
final result = await Get.dialog<bool>(
  ConfirmationDialog(),
);
if (result == true) {
  // Handle confirmation
}
```

### Bottom Sheets
```dart
// Show bottom sheet
Get.bottomSheet(
  Container(
    height: 200,
    child: Column(
      children: [
        Text('Bottom Sheet Content'),
        ElevatedButton(
          onPressed: () => Get.back(),
          child: Text('Close'),
        ),
      ],
    ),
  ),
);

// Show modal bottom sheet
Get.bottomSheet(
  ModalBottomSheet(),
  isScrollControlled: true,
  backgroundColor: Colors.transparent,
);
```

